Interpretation

Supposing a rectilinear propagation of ultrasonic waves all recorded echo travel times were converted into distances by using the subsequent speeds of sound:

1817.4 m/s ( 5962.7 ft/s) to 1821.2 m/s ( 5975.2 ft/s) in brine (measured)

In the case of recording several echoes along one trace of echo signals, the representative echo signal was selected according to the level of amplitude, transmission time, density of measured points and the shape of the cavern.



